I chose this rating for a number of reasons.

1.) I understand Tyler Perry is trying to send positive messages, but I'm ready for something new. All of his plays are too similar. He recycles some of the same jokes and I even heard some jokes off of Martin.

2.) I think Tamar is a great actress, but she annoyed the BLANK out of me. I understand she's playing the role of a sixteen year old girl but she was a little too extra for me; whining and complaining.

3.)I I'm sick of seeing the same people in plays. I wanna see a fresh (talented) face.

I'm convinced, Palmer Williams needs his own show. I own every Tyler Perry play and Palmer Williams is brilliant in them all. This play is awesome and reminiscent of the true community experience. The bond between between the neighbors reminds me of the neighborhood I grew up in. The music is incredible, Cheryl Pepsi Riley, outstanding, D'Atra Hicks, magnificent. For those of you that enjoyed this play, I also recommend "Marriage Counselor". "Laugh To Keep From Crying" is truely one of those plays you watch that will quickly lift you out of a spirit of depression and is hilarious. Tyler has done it again and I am proud to be a fan of his work.
